response.overview: Returning after two sell-out runs at Soho Theatre, global sensation Jazz Emu is back with his virtuoso musical spectacular. 'This is a work of genius' ***** (Telegraph). In 2016, Jazz Emu played the biggest gig he'd ever landed at the Helsinki Velodrome. But during his between-song patter, he carelessly insulted one of his biggest fans. Now he's back to clear his name and regain his former glory. Will he be able to get every single person in the world to like him? Or is it time for him to face the music?
response.title: Jazz Emu: You Shouldn't Have
